Container Instance: EC2 Server where the container runs.
Tasks: each container can be called as task.
Rask definition: Image,CPU,Memory
Service: Similar to docker service which can deploy a complete solution.


====>Login to ec2 instance

check docker version
#docker info

#docker ps
u will seee one predeployed container named ecs agent.

ECR: container Registry / images repository

Lets create new container
Go to task definitons.
go to create a new task
click EC2(among fargate and ec2)
We create a task definition as json file.

We have the file ECStaskDef1.json file with us.

Now enter all details in task definitions
Give the json file inside "configure via json"

Then run task.
You can find ip to nginx server in details of task in task definition.



